DSA-004A

## `if`, `else`, `else if`

---

### ðŸ§  **What is it?**

Used to **make decisions** in code.

Runs different blocks **based on conditions**.

---

### ðŸ§© **Syntax:**

```java
if (condition) {
    // Runs if condition is true
} else {
    // Runs if condition is false
}
```

âž¡ **Multiple checks:**

```java
if (condition1) {
    // true block 1
} else if (condition2) {
    // true block 2
} else {
    // runs if none is true
}
```

---

### ðŸ“Œ **Example:**

```java
int marks = 80;

if (marks >= 90) {
    System.out.println("Grade A");
} else if (marks >= 75) {
    System.out.println("Grade B");
} else {
    System.out.println("Grade C");
}
```

---

### ðŸ§  **1 Line Logic:**

> "Check conditions top to bottom and run the first block that is true."
> 

---

### âœ… **When to Use:**

- Result: Pass / Fail
- Check the largest numbers
- Odd or Even
- Age-based decisions
- Tax, salary slabs, etc.

---

### ðŸ§  Tips:

- Only 1 block runs
- Use `{}` even for single-line
- `else if` is optional
- Always end with `else` if needed

